Package: smartr
Type: Package
Title: Smart Ways to Run Bayesian Models on JATOS Data
Version: 0.2.7
Authors@R: c(
    person("Chenyu", "Li", email = "chenyu.li.hz@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Joscha", "Dutli", email = "joscha.dutli@psychologie.uzh.ch", role = c("aut"))
  )
Description: A comprehensive toolkit for processing JATOS (Just Another Tool for 
    Online Studies) data and fitting Bayesian models. The package provides 
    functions for data retrieval, preprocessing, model fitting with 'brms', 
    and advanced post-processing including Bayes factor computation and 
    pairwise comparisons of estimated marginal means. It streamlines the 
    workflow from raw experimental data to publication-ready Bayesian analysis 
    results, with special focus on cognitive and psychological research data.
